## Hooks

DataSources support lifecycle hooks for query modification, validation, and side effects.

### Query Hooks

```typescript
export const EntityDataSource: DataSource<Entity> = {
  ...DefaultDataSource,
  // ... attributes and access ...

  // Modify query object before execution
  preQuery: async ({ query, session, client }) => {
    // Add user-specific filter for non-admins
    if (!session.user.roles.includes('admin')) {
      query.filters = [...(query.filters || []), { userId: { is: session.user.id } }];
    }
    return query;
  },

  // Advanced: Modify SQL query directly (use sparingly)
  preQuery2: ({ query, sql, params, session, client }) => {
    const planId = query.match?.planId;
    if (planId) {
      params.push(planId);
      sql = sql.replace('WHERE', `WHERE plan_id = $${params.length} AND`);
    }
    return { sql, params };
  },

  // Process query results before returning
  postQuery: async ({ query, rows, session, client }) => {
    // Add computed fields, filter sensitive data, etc.
    return rows.map(row => ({
      ...row,
      displayName: `${row.firstName} ${row.lastName}`,
    }));
  },
};
```

### Insert/Update/Delete Hooks

```typescript
import { UserError } from 'venky-core/common';

export const EntityDataSource: DataSource<Entity> = {
  ...DefaultDataSource,

  // Validate and modify before insert
  // Note: Audit columns (createdAt, createdBy) are set automatically by the framework
  beforeInsert: async ({ rows, session, client }) => {
    for (const row of rows) {
      if (!row.name?.trim()) {
        throw new UserError('Name is required');
      }
      // Set defaults that aren't handled by DataSource defaultValue
      if (!row.status) {
        row.status = 'draft';
      }
    }
    return {
      rows,
      // skipDML: true  // Optional: skip actual insert (for custom handling)
    };
  },

  // Post-process after insert
  afterInsert: async ({ rows, session, client }) => {
    // Send notifications, create related records, etc.
    // Runs within same transaction
    return rows;
  },

  // Validate and modify before update
  // Note: Audit columns (updatedAt, updatedBy) are set automatically by the framework
  beforeUpdate: async ({ rows, session, client }) => {
    for (const row of rows) {
      // Example: set publishedAt when status changes to published
      if (row.status === 'published' && !row.publishedAt) {
        row.publishedAt = new Date().toISOString();
      }
    }
    return { rows };
  },

  // Post-process after update
  afterUpdate: async ({ rows, session, client }) => {
    // Audit logging, cache invalidation, etc.
    return rows;
  },

  // Validate before delete
  beforeDelete: async ({ rows, session, client }) => {
    // Check if delete is allowed
    for (const row of rows) {
      if (row.isProtected) {
        throw new UserError('Cannot delete protected records');
      }
    }
    return rows;
  },

  // Post-process after delete - cascade delete related records
  afterDelete: async ({ rows, session, client }) => {
    // Cleanup related data, notifications, etc.
    return rows;
  },

  // Validate single row (called during validation)
  validateOne: async ({ row, session, client }) => {
    // Custom validation logic
    return row;
  },
};
```

### Hook Reference

| Hook | When | Returns |
|------|------|---------|
| `preQuery` | Before query execution | Modified `Query<T>` |
| `preQuery2` | After preQuery, before SQL execution | `{ sql, params }` |
| `postQuery` | After query results | Modified `DBRow<T>[]` |
| `beforeInsert` | Before insert | `{ rows, skipDML? }` |
| `afterInsert` | After insert | `DBRow<T>[]` |
| `beforeUpdate` | Before update | `{ rows, skipDML? }` |
| `afterUpdate` | After update | `DBRow<T>[]` |
| `beforeDelete` | Before delete | `DBRow<T>[]` |
| `afterDelete` | After delete | `DBRow<T>[]` |
| `validateOne` | Row validation | `Row<T>` |

### Cascade Delete Pattern (afterDelete)

Use `afterDelete` to cascade delete related records:

```typescript
import type { DataSource, DBRow } from 'venky-core/common';
import { UserError } from 'venky-core/common';
import { DefaultAttribute, DefaultDataSource, DefaultFullAccess } from 'venky-core/ds';
import type { PgPoolClient } from 'venky-core/server';
import type { Session } from 'venky-core/auth';
import type { Project } from '@/lib/common/ds/types/module/Project';

export const ProjectDS: DataSource<Project> = {
  ...DefaultDataSource,
  // ... attributes and access ...

  async afterDelete(props: {
    rows: DBRow<Project>[];
    session: Session;
    client: PgPoolClient;
  }): Promise<DBRow<Project>[]> {
    const { client, rows } = props;

    if (rows.length === 0) {
      return rows;
    }

    // Prevent bulk delete (optional safety check)
    if (rows.length > 1) {
      throw new UserError('Bulk deletion is not supported. Please delete one at a time.');
    }

    const projectId = rows[0].projectId;
    if (!projectId) {
      return rows;
    }

    // Cascade delete related records
    await client.query(`DELETE FROM project_tasks WHERE project_id = $1`, [projectId]);
    await client.query(`DELETE FROM project_roles WHERE project_id = $1`, [projectId]);

    return rows;
  },
};
```

**Important notes for `afterDelete`:**
- Use `DBRow<T>` (not `Row<T>`) for the rows type
- Import `Session` from `venky-core/auth` (not `venky-core/server`)
- Add explicit return type `Promise<DBRow<T>[]>`
- Runs within the same transaction as the delete
- Consider adding bulk delete prevention for safety

### Hook Context

- `session` - Current user session with roles, user info
- `client` - Database transaction client (same transaction as main operation)
- Throwing `UserError` shows message to user and rolls back transaction
- Throwing other errors logs to server and shows generic error to user
- `skipDML: true` in beforeInsert/beforeUpdate skips the actual DML (for custom handling)

## Registration

Add to module index and main index:

```typescript
// src/lib/server/ds/defs/module/index.ts
export { EntityDataSource } from './EntityDS';

// src/lib/server/ds/defs/index.ts
import { EntityDataSource } from './module';

const allDataSources = {
  // ... existing
  Entity: EntityDataSource,
};
```
